    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nUsing 0.11.0 with `vim.diagnostic.config({ virtual_lines = true })` + `set number cpoptions+=n` results in the column indicator being misaligned.\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```sh\nnvim --clean -c 'set cpoptions+=n | set number' -c 'normal 7i01234 56789 ' -c 'normal yy2p' -c 'lua vim.diagnostic.config({ virtual_lines = true })' -c 'lua vim.diagnostic.set(1, 0, { { lnum = 1, col = 6, message = \"testing testing\" } })'\n```\n\n#### Observe\n\n##### with `set nonumber`\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2b87994f-e1a0-4095-b45c-fc3db68c674e)\n\n##### with `set number`\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/461a8348-c42c-4a35-976c-cdbee91f4662)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI would expect the diagnostic to point to the correct column in both cases. It works without `cpoptions+=n` set. The `n` option is useful for merging `showbreak` with the number column.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 14.7\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nTerminal.app\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nMacPorts",
